@NODE "HistoryK"
@TITLE "Release V0.11"
@NEXT "HistoryL"
@PREV "HistoryJ"
@TOC "HistoryLog"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Anleitung zu Laplace --------------------------------------- Release V0.11 -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "HistoryLog" "Release V0.11"
@{B}Release V0.11@{UB}  (beta-release) released 27.2.1998

 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}29.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 2 @{UI}: You can use @{I}array(...) @{UI} for creating arrays again.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}30.1.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 3 @{UI}:  You can now  edit some global  plotter settings. These  are
      used, when a new plotter is opened. If you modify some local plot-
      ter settings, the global settings are updated, too. So you  always
      get the settings of the last plotter, if you open a new one.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}2.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 4 @{UI}: Restructured internal  plotter handling, making further  ex-
      tensions easier.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 5 @{UI}: Reimplemented image caching for faster display update. Still
      to be improved.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 6  @{UI}: Added  @{B}prompt@{UB}, @{B}seperator  thickness@{UB} and  @{B}center results@{UB}  to
      preferences. These were options before, what didn't make sense...
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}3.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 7 @{UI}: Plotter settings for  functions (color, precision etc.) are
      now saved, too.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 8 @{UI}: You can now remove functions from a plotter in the settings
      window.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 9 @{UI}: Added  the ability to plot  functions @{I}[x(t),y(t)], t=a...b @{UI}
      instead of normal functions ...[x,y(x)], x=a...b
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 10 @{UI}: Cool!! Animated Lissajous-figures.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}4.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 11 @{UI}: Changed syntax of some functions, now using intervals:
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} genarray(a=1 .. 2, f(a))
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} genvector(a=1 .. 2, f(a))
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} genmatrix(a=1 .. 2, b=1 .. 2, f(a,b))
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 12 @{UI}: Function graph thickness  implemented. Currently only 1, 2
      or 3.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 13  @{UI}: New  class @{B}integral@{UB}.  Currently  there are  no operations
      available for it, but numerical integration is comming up next.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 14 @{UI}: Repaired my shoes... no money for new ones.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 15  @{UI}: And  here it  is... Numerical  integration. Try  something
      like:
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} A = integral( x^2, x=0..1 )
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} nint(A)
         Adjust precision with @{B}$intprec@{UB}, the higher the better.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}5.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 16 @{UI}: Now you can use intervals in indeces: @{I}A[2 .. 3, 2 .. 3] @{UI} ->
      fetch a 2x2 matrix from the bigger matrix @{I}A @{UI}
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}6.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 17 @{UI}: Now generates an error message, if you use arguments for a
      reference, which is itself an argument,  e.g. @{I}f(x) = x(2) @{UI}. Thanx
      to Myk Hoole for is bug report.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 18 @{UI}: Cursor is now blinking again...
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 19 @{UI}: Fonts and colors  are now updated correctly, when  modified
      in the preferences.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 20 @{UI}: Display  for greek letters in  the preferences window used
      wrong font.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}16.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 21 @{UI}: As reported, the  startup window still causes problems.  If
      nothing helps, it can be turned off completly.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 22 @{UI}: Fixed  a bug when displaying  things like @{I}x ^  1 / a @{UI}.  Re-
      ported by Rolf Kabbe.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 23  @{UI}: Fixed  a bug  of the  vector product.  Reported by  Sascha
      Werth.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 24 @{UI}: It is now possible to export a project as ASCII even with-
      out a keyfile. The import function is disabled instead.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}17.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 25 @{UI}: You can set the x-range directly with with @{I}plot() @{UI} command:
      @{I}plot(f(x), x=a..b) @{UI}
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}18.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 26 @{UI}: @{I}derive(x ^ x, x) @{UI}  was wrong. Not the bug reported by Rolf
      Kabbe, but is report was a hint...
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 27 @{UI}: Simplification of  @{I}x ^ a+1 @{UI} caused  an endless loop. @{I}This @{UI}
      was the bug reported by Rolf Kabbe.
 @{B}∑@{UB} @{B}21.2.1998@{UB}:
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 28 @{UI}: Improved syntax of @{I}animate() @{UI}, e.g.
      @{B}@{BG FILL}@{FG FILLTEXT}>@{UB}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{FG TEXT} animate(f(x,t), x=-1..1, t=0..10)
         Intervals are optional.
    @{B}∑@{UB} @{I}ş 29 @{UI}: Fixed and improved image caching (for buttons and  Pierre's
      face).


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}----------------------------------------------------------------- © bei P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
